<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-31T17:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-31T17:16:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/6067</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-31T18:00:00-04:16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Minister of Marine assured me that if Germany’s reply to Argentine
                                demands is not unconditional acceptance, Argentina will declare war.
                                If Germany accepts, laws of Argentina will be suspended in order to
                                facilitate registration of vessels under Argentine flag.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SFJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>